article.headline: Fresno St. 86, Montana St. 74
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Hector Hernandez scored 20 points and Kevin Bell had 18 points and 10 assists Wednesday night as Fresno State defeated Montana State 86-74. Brian Harvey added 18 points for the Bulldogs (3-2), who converted 27 of 30 free throws to snap a two-game losing streak. Fresno State entered the game shooting 61.4 percent from the line. Carlos Taylor scored a game-high 25 points for Montana State (2-3), and Divaldo Mbunga added 22 points and eight rebounds. Fresno State enjoyed a comfortable lead for most of the game until Branden Johnson's 3-pointer with 5:30 left pulled the Bobcats to within 73-68. Bell took over from there with assists on three straight possessions to keep the Bulldogs in front. The senior point guard fed the ball inside to Hernandez for a jump hook, then found Tyson Parker on the perimeter for an open 3-pointer. Bell capped the surge by lobbing the ball to Shawn Taylor for an alleyoop dunk, giving Fresno State an 84-70 lead with 1:43 left. Hernandez finished a career-best 10 of 10 from the free-throw line. Fresno State led 47-30 at halftime thanks to a 13-0 run late in the period. Bell sparked the rally by stealing the ball at midcourt from Casey Durham and driving for a layup. On the Bulldogs' next possession, Bell found Harvey for an open 3-pointer. Harvey led all scorers with 13 first-half points, going 3 of 5 from beyond the arc. Fresno State played its first game without the injured Dwight O'Neil, the Bulldogs' second leading scorer. O'Neil is expected to miss the next two months with a broken wrist.
